The paper addresses a routing problem with a Dubins vehicle, which is a common topic in robotics and control systems (cs.RO). The proposed method utilizes a regression model to estimate the length of the optimal Dubins path, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.AI). The problem also involves optimization and control of the vehicle's heading angles, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The use of a sliding window technique and cache for already computed results suggests a focus on efficient algorithms and data structures, which could be categorized as machine learning (cs.LG) or computer vision (cs.CV) depending on the specific application.
